Author: kayteesays
Text: So I'd recommend some ibuprofen, plenty of fluids, and maybe trying some of these: [https://www.colgate.com/en-us/oral-health/conditions/temporomandibular-disorder/tmj-massage-to-relieve-jaw-pain-1115](https://www.colgate.com/en-us/oral-health/conditions/temporomandibular-disorder/tmj-massage-to-relieve-jaw-pain-1115)  &#x200B;  Also try to avoid purging for awhile. (Obviously easier said than done.) If none of that helps and you're still hurting this badly in a few more days, give your dentist a call.   &#x200B;  &#x200B;

Author: TotallyNotARadar
Text: I don't purge but I guess I have really really weak enamel and so when I drink a ridiculous amount of soda my teeth hurt for a solid few days. It gets better after a while though usually. Ibuprofen helps too. If it doesn't go away within like a week and you're worried I'd check in with a dentist of course.
